  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A study using characteristics on ultrasound to predict response to intraarticular steroid
      injections in patients with knee osteoarthritis. The hypothesis is that patients with
      inflammation on ultrasound will have a better response to corticosteroid injections compared
      to patients without inflammation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
